[1] Georgia
Date: Tue 26 Mar 2013
Source: Rocbalt [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.rosbalt.ru/exussr/2013/03/26/1110342.html


The number of measles cases in Georgia is incasing. 142 of 403 cases have been hospitalized, according to the National Centre for Disease Control of Public Health Department of the Republic. Compared with statistics from previous years, in 2013 Georgia recorded a significant increase in prevalence of measles. A representative of the National Centre for Disease Control and Public Health, Amiran Gamkrelidze, said that measles immunization will be available without charge for all children and individuals under the age of 30.

According to Georgia Online, measles in Georgia has infected 162 persons aged 20 to 29 years of age. Currently, 96 are older than 30 years of age, 37 are adolescents (15 to 19 years), 22 are teenagers (10-14 years), 17 are children (aged 5 to 9 years) and 47 are infants aged from one to 4 years. In addition, measles was diagnosed in 22 babies.

