[6] Pakistan (Punjab)
Date: Mon 25 Mar 2013
Source: Daily Times, APP report [edited]
http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2013%5C03%5C25%5Cstory_25-3-2013_pg13_6


Over 6000 cases of measles were reported in 4 months in different parts of Punjab, mostly in Lahore, during the current surveillance drive, stated Director Health Services for EPI Punjab, Dr Tanveer Ahmed. 60-70 cases of measles are being reported every day in different parts of the province, he added. He stated further that 19 deaths of children had been reported so far including in Gujranwala, Rajanpur, Rahim Yar Khan, Kasur and Lahore district.

"The vaccination and surveillance drive has been stepped up to control the threat. It is also part of the strategy to mop up and vaccinate areas with measles patients," said the director. He said that intensive vaccination was also launched in Rahim Yar Khan and adjoining tehsils [an administrative division - CopyEd.MSP] near the Sindh border so that the virus will be prevented from spreading into Punjab. Dr Ahmed said that measles vaccination was available at all hospitals in Lahore and that parents should get their children, up to the age of 5, vaccinated without delay.

